ElevatedButton(
                      style: ElevatedButton.styleFrom(
                        backgroundColor: Colors.orange,
                        foregroundColor: Colors.black,
                        minimumSize: Size(150, 50),          // at least will take this size "or more depends on the text of the button"
                        // fixedSize: Size(150, 50),        // fixed size no matter the length of the text
                      ),
                      onPressed: () {},
                      child: Text(
                        'Add 1 Point',
                        style: TextStyle(color: Colors.black, fontSize: 24),
                      ),
                    ),




when call ElevatedButton() Widget,   it must accept required function     and  set  onPressed parameter 
onPressed  =>> is the action what will happen when u press this Button



void actionButton(){}
ElevatedButton(
  onPressed:  (){},        //    (){}    is  anonymous Function,  cuz we don't need to call this function again
  // onPressed: actionButton, // or u can put normal function, but note u pass the function,  NOT Call it,  so u can't make it like this   onPressed: actionButton() // error u can't put (), cuz u pass the function as a value not calling it
)
